@Node How2Use "How to use the poke guide"

Well, this is really easy peasy...


   - Just start ZXAM (the poke guide supports no other emulator).

   - Load the game you want to play, but do NOT run it. It is crucial
     that the emulation has been stopped!

   - Go to the poke list and search for the game you have currently
     loaded. If it is not there, well, bad luck to you... :)

   - If you've found it, just move the mouse towards the box and klick
     on it.

   - All games marked with a "->" open a sub list. You can select some
     more different pokes.

   - All games marked with a "?>" open a sub list with some nice hints.

   - Yeah, that was all the hard work. You now just have to start the
     emulation... :-)


I tried very hard to make no typo while typing all the  pokes  down...
But  - as nobody - i am not perfect at all. It is possible that a poke
does not work or even crash your emulated spectrum, since most of  the
pokes in this list are not checked.

The function of some pokes are not known, too... But i think you  will
detect their function yourself.


If you have more pokes, better pokes or whatsoever, please  feel  free
to @{" contact " LINK Address} me...

I'm also looking for comments on the pokes. Do they work?


@EndNode
@Node Address "Get in contact with me !!!"

If you've found  some  bad  pokes,  found  out  the  function  of  the
anonymous  pokes, have some additions or even new or much better pokes
or just want to swap poke lists, PLEEEEEEZE  contact  me  immediately!
This  poke  guide  lives  by YOUR help only! The more you help me, the
better this guide will be finally!!!

You can contact me, too, if you tested some pokes (even if they did or
didn't work)...

But remember: if you want to send me some new pokes, you  always  have
to  send the full game name, the poke and its function... I'll include
your name into the greetings list! :-)

You can also send me a game you want to have POKEs for, and  i'll  see
what i can do... :-)


Well, i just reached my aim to get 500 pokes! YEAH! I even exceeded it
by 147 pokes! But i wonder if it is possible to get @{B}800@{UB} pokes...



@{B}I prefer E-Mails. Send them to:@{UB}

